BezierPoint - Class in graphicslib3D.editors
This class is a helper class supporting the SurfacePatchDialog; it is not intended to be used directly.
BezierPoint() - Constructor for class graphicslib3D.editors.BezierPoint
Base constructor; all coordinates are initialized to 0, and the point size is set to 8 pixels in length.
BezierPoint(double, double, double) - Constructor for class graphicslib3D.editors.BezierPoint
First overloaded constructor; both origin and location coordinates are set to the same passed values.
BRONZE - Static variable in class graphicslib3D.Material
A predefined material with the ambient, diffuse, specular, and shininess characteristics of Bronze.
